# State Management

## Chrome Storage (Persistent)
- Use `chrome.storage.local` for user preferences and cached data
- Use `chrome.storage.session` for temporary session state
- NEVER use `chrome.storage.sync` for clinical data (size limits + sync risks)
- Define storage schemas with Zod for runtime validation on read/write
- All storage keys: prefixed with `sentra_` namespace

## React State (Ephemeral)
- Local UI state: `useState` — component-scoped, not shared
- Shared state: Zustand store with typed slices
- Server/async state: TanStack Query with proper stale/cache config
- URL state: `useSearchParams` for shareable/bookmarkable state

## State Architecture
```
chrome.storage.local  →  Zustand hydration  →  React components
     (disk)               (memory)               (UI)
```

## Rules
- Single source of truth per data domain — no duplicated state
- Zustand stores: one per domain (`usePatientStore`, `useSettingsStore`)
- Immutable updates only — never mutate state directly
- Storage migrations: version your storage schema, handle upgrades gracefully
- Clinical state MUST be read-only in the frontend — mutations via background script only
